Extractions during facials are actually way more beneficial than you know! 

Extractions, when done correctly, can clear closed comedones remove whiteheads and blackheads, and give your skin a newer, fresher foundation for your skincare products to penetrate. They give an even, clear complexion, less congestion, better product absorption and efficacy, and less breakouts in the future.

Benefits include:

✨Helps maintain clear skin
✨Deeply cleanses pores
✨Smoothes out bumps
✨Safe when performed by a professional
✨Products penetrate more efficiently

🌟 Are you purging or breaking out?

Purging is:

- Acne is triggered by active ingredients accelerating cellular turnover.
- It often happens when introducing a new product.
- It manifests as clusters of blackheads or whiteheads. Anything coming to the surface of the skin. 
- Be patient; skin purging can typically last about 4-8 weeks. Skin purging can look different for everyone. 

💥 Breakouts on the other hand, are:

- Acne resulting from clogged pores.
- Caused by comedogenic ingredients, hormones, lack of exfoliation, or excess oil.
- Typically seen as whiteheads, blackheads, or tender bumps.
- Consider consulting a skincare specialist for a personalized regimen. 🧴🔍

The love I have for others and the passion to help people achieve their skin goals fill my heart with so much joy. Skin By You is about loving the skin that you're in, embracing your own unique self, and it's all about you because you are the hero in your skincare journey, and I'm simply here to guide you.

I am so grateful for the amazing career I chose and for the most amazing clients. I love making people feel confident and telling them how beautiful they are. Double cleansing is twice as nice! 🫧 

Your first cleanse is going to remove any surface level oil, dirt, or makeup on the skin & your second cleanse is going to be the one that properly cleanses your skin or to target your specific skincare concern. 🙌🏽

Double cleansing prevents future breakouts from forming and allows your products following after your cleanse to work more efficiently. 👏🏽

ACNE SCARS ARE NOT FOREVER! 🫶🏽

Microneedling, advanced facials, and chemical peels are some of my favorite treatments to improve acne scarring! ✨

* @skinpen Microneedling stimulates collagen production, promoting skin regeneration and minimizing the appearance of scars. This will take a series of 3-6 treatments for optimal results! 

* Advanced facials, such as @hydrafacial improves by the help of advanced exfoliation and is tailored to individual skin needs, with its cutting-edge technologies to address specific scarring concerns.

* Chemical peels such as @theperfectdermapeel or @bioskin_aesthetics_inc , with their exfoliating power, can fade hyperpigmentation and even out skin tone, diminishing the visibility of acne scars over time.

* Additionally, incorporating skincare products with Tyrosinase inhibitors (aka pigment inhibitors) is key for both preventing and correcting acne scarring. Ingredients like Tranexamic acid, vitamin C, and alpha arbutin are only a few ingredients that help inhibit melanin production, reducing the risk of post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation. My personal favorite skincare product is Even Tone Correcting Serum from Skinbetter which you can shop the link in my bio! Consistent use of these products complements professional treatments, ensuring the BEST results! 🫶🏽
